entry.tran: （英国下院的）后座议员，普通议员
entry.def: A backbencher is a Member of Parliament who is not a minister and who does not hold an official position in their political party.

example.tran: 保守党下院资深后座议员

means.word_mean: 1. a member of the House of Commons who is not a party leader
